The reasons why someone may decide to launch their own firm or become an entrepreneur are referred to as push and pull considerations. Push factors are what steer someone away from regular work, such unhappiness with a present position or a desire for greater freedom. Pull factors, on the other side, are motivations for starting a business, such as the chance for financial gain or the freedom to work for oneself. Together, these elements may have an impact on a person's choice to pursue entrepreneurship and may contribute to a company's success or failure. 